    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.35b.11"/>
                
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>A sunflower, with 20 funnel-shaped figures beneath</figDesc>
                </figure>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        Wednesday
                        <note type="cuatorial">7/27/71</note>
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I saw you recently on the Dick Cavet<sic>Cavett</sic> show, &amp; quite frankly I enjoyed the program more than any other I have seen on television. It was extremely informative because I really know nothing of the American Indian. (Just what was written in history books) I would like to learn more about the Cheyenne Indians. I know you're terribly busy, but I thought perhaps if you had time you could refer me to some books 
                
                <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
                
                    which might help me. My grandfather was half Cheyenne &amp; he died when I was very young. So unfortunately I know very little about that part of my heritage. My son &amp; daughter are very small now, but I want them to grow up respecting the indian &amp; <unclear>their</unclear> way of life as well as that of the white man. I would also like to know where the Cheyenne Reservation is becuase I would also like to write to them. If something can be done to help these magnificent people I will gladly do whatever I 
                
                <fw type="curatorial">11</fw>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.35b.12"/>
                
                <fw type="authorial">-3-</fw>
                
                    can. Thank you for reading the letter. If you can help me I will be eternally grateful.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Mrs. Mark Montgomery</signed>
                    <add>
                        <note>
                            <address>
                                <addrLine>715 Northwest 36th St.</addrLine> 
                                <addrLine>Gainesville, Florida 82001</addrLine>
                            </address>
                        </note>
                    </add>
                </closer>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">12</fw>
                
            </div1>
